This file explains how to start Freja in different debug modes
==============================================================
Options: -d -s -u -v

-d	all (1-100) debug switches are set

-s	Is to be directly followed by one or more (space-seperated) digits
	- e.g. "-s1 44 56 100 0" - and terminated by a zero if further
	arguments are given. Detailed documentation of the individual switches
	is given below.

	example usage:		freja -s1
	or: 			freja -s1 0 foo

-u	make userdata verbose

-v	make designenv verbose

Switches:
---------
1:  buttons+menues for debugging become available (e.g. in the View Menu)
17: save, load, quit, etc. (file I/O)
12: focus
20: turn on property diagrams
30: callback
40: communication with Sif
50: specialisation
51: binding connector
52: pattern variable connector
53: association
54: aggregation
60: AST-edit (via Sif)
70: display, detail, abstract etc.
80: textedit
90: tree prettyprint
99: object diagrams
100: turn off autosave

